text: Kathleen "Kathy" Mattea (born June 21, 1959, West Virginia) is an American Celtic recording artist and country musician. She had multiple strong-charting singles. Some of them are Eighteen Wheels and a Dozen Roses and Where've You Been. Her career began in 1983.
